  <p>Looking through your parents' attic, you find a cabinet you've never seen before. You open it up and find shelves full of antique wooden puzzles. Well, guess you know your plans for this evening.</p>
<h4>1. Leaping Frogs</h4>
<p>Click on a blve block to move it to the right, andclick on a red block to move it to the left. Blockscan hop over another block ifthere is an adjacentempty space to land on. Move all red blocks tothe left and all blve blocks to the right to win.</p>
<h4>2. 15 puzzle</h4>
<p>Click on a tile to slide it.Tiles can slide horizontallyand vertically, and theremust be a space availablefor the tile to move. To win,manipulate the tiles so thatthe numbers are in order.</p>
<h4>3. Peg Solitaire</h4>
<p>Click on a marble, and it will hop over an adjacentmarble into an empty space. The adjacent marbleis then removed. To win, remove all the marblesfrom the board until there is one marble left.</p>
<h4>4. Tower of Hanoi</h4>
<p>Click on a peg to pick up the top ring. Then,click on another peg to drop the ring.Ringscannot be placed on smaller rings. To win,move the entire tower to the rightmost peg.</p>
<h4>5. Lights Out</h4>
<p>Click on a light to turn it onor off. Adjacent lights willalso switch. To win, torn offall the lights on the board.</p>
<h4>6. English16</h4>
<p>Click on a piece to move it to an empty space.Pieces can hop over others. Red pieces canonly move right, while black only moves left.To win, move all red pieces to the right side ofthe board and move all black pieces to the left(In easy mode, pieces can move in all directions)</p>
